This paper discusses the issues of privacy, security, and data ownership, which are closely related to the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a consent management system for data access, which involves managing and storing data, making it relevant to the field of databases (cs.DB) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The system also requires efficient data processing and management, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper presents a scalable system, which involves software engineering and system design (cs.SE).
